724902f-a.text:
York Avenue (Avenue A), east side, from 71st to 74th Streets, showing the new P. Lorillard factory, erected around 1923 where the old Charles C. Clausen Malt House stood since around 1885.
September 15, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

714311f-a.text:
501-7 East 71st Street, at N.E. corner of York avenue. In the foreground is the excavation for the Cornell Medical College-New York Hospital.
July 31, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.

724901f-b.text:
(1)
York Ave., (Ave. A), west side, north from East 71st Street. Note the church of the Redemptionist Fathers of New York at No. 1337 York Ave., between East 71st and 72nd Streets.
September 25, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
Showing a closer view of the aforementioned Church.
September 25, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
